<tool id="general_matrix_tool" name="Matrix" version="@TOOL_VERSION@+galaxy@VERSION_SUFFIX@" profile="@PROFILE@">
  <description> generation tool</description>
  <creator>
   <organization name="INFRAFRONTIER GmbH" url="https://www.infrafrontier.eu/" email="info@infrafrontier.eu" />
   <person name="Andrea Furlani" email="andrea.furlani@infrafrontier.eu" />
   <person name="Philipp Gormanns" email="philipp.gormanns@infrafrontier.eu" />
  </creator>
  <requirements>
    <requirement type="package" version="3.10">python</requirement>
    <requirement type="package" version="2.2.3">pandas</requirement>
  </requirements>
  <command detect_errors="exit_code">
	  <![CDATA[python3 '$__tool_directory__/matrices.py' '$input' '$lab_col' '$count_col' '$output1' '$output2']]>
  </command>
  <inputs>
          <param name="input" type="data" format="tabular,txt" label="Input file:" help="Enter a file containing the input table"/>
          <param name="lab_col" type="integer" label="Labels column" value="0" help="Enter the index of the column with the elements that will be used as labels"/>
          <param name="count_col" type="integer" label="Count column" value="0" help="Enter the index of the column with the elements that will be used for the count"/>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
	  <data format="tabular" name="output1" label="Names matrix"/>
	  <data format="tabular" name="output2" label="Count matrix"/>
  </outputs>
  <tests>
    <test>
      <param name="input" value="pheno_retr_50.txt" ftype="txt"/>
      <param name="lab_col" value="0"/>
      <param name="count_col" value="1"/>
      <output name="output1" file="name_matrix.tsv" ftype="tabular"/>
      <output name="output2" file="count_matrix.tsv" ftype="tabular"/>
    </test>
  </tests>
  <help><![CDATA[
    
	  
    **What it does**

    This tool performs a pairwise overlap analysis between entities associated with lists of values. 
    It is designed to identify and quantify shared elements between all pairs of entities in a dataset.
    A common use case is a table where each row represents an entity (e.g. a gene, disease, strain, sample, or any other identifier) and one column contains a comma-separated list of associated elements. 
    The tool compares all entities against each other and determines which elements they have in common.
    The output consists of two matrices:

    - Count matrix: contains the number of shared elements for each pair of entities.
    - Name matrix: contains the actual shared elements for each pair of entities.

    These matrices can be used for downstream analyses, similarity assessments, clustering approaches, or visualization workflows.
    After selecting the input file, the user must specify:

    - the column index containing the entity labels (used for both matrix axes);
    - the column index containing the comma-separated elements to be compared.

    Column indices start at 0.

    **Input requirements**

    The input table should already be aggregated by the label column, meaning that each entity should appear only once. The comparison column must contain a comma-separated list of values.
    For example, a gene could be associated with a list of phenotypes, a disease with a list of genes, or a sample with a list of detected features. However, the tool is intentionally generic and can be applied to any tabular dataset that follows this structure.
    
    **Example**
    
    Given the following table as input:

    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                G1                       |                 N1                    |              P1,P2,P3,P4                |                12.5                   |                   123                   |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                G2                       |                 N2                    |              P3,P5                      |                26.0                   |                   234                   |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                G3                       |                 N3                    |              P1,P3,P5                   |                35.3                   |                   176                   |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                G4                       |                 N4                    |              P6                         |                00.1                   |                   676                   |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+

    The user chooses column 0 for the labels and column 2 for the elements to be compared.
    The resulting matrices will be the following:
    
    |

    -Matrix containing shared element names/IDs

    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 x                       |                 G1                    |                  G2                     |                 G3                    |                  G4                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G1                      |             P1,P2,P3,P4               |                  P3                     |                 P1                    |                 None                    |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G2                      |                 P3                    |                 P3,P5                   |                P3,P5                  |                 None                    |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G3                      |                P1,P5                  |                 P3,P5                   |               P1,P3,P5                |                 None                    |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G4                      |                None                   |                  None                   |                 None                  |                  P6                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    
    |

    -Matrix containing overlap counts

    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 x                       |                 G1                    |                  G2                     |                 G3                    |                  G4                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G1                      |                 4                     |                  1                      |                 1                     |                   0                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G2                      |                 1                     |                  2                      |                 2                     |                   0                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G3                      |                 2                     |                  2                      |                 3                     |                   0                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+
    |                 G4                      |                 0                     |                  0                      |                 0                     |                   1                     |
    +-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+---------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+

    |
    |
    
